msgSnippet: JUnit is for Testing Framework for Java that every one know s and i hope you also. For .Net there is Testing Framework same as JUnit called NUnit. Data Link.
messageBody:
JUnit is for Testing Framework for Java that every one know's and i hope you also.

For .Net there is Testing Framework same as JUnit called NUnit.

Data Link.
http://www.nunit.org/

Go to above link for more information about .Net Unit Testing Framework.

Regards,
Riesh Suthar.

nitin pallan <focus_on_me21@...> wrote: Hi i m nitin pallan. I m working as a software tester for the last 7 months. Now i am in a stage, that my organisation is asking me to study how to work with junit for a project. I dont know the exact process. I have gone thru some codings shown the helping web sites. U can u just help me out in knowing the entire process of how a Junit testing can be done. And on what all kind of languages it can be done. Also just tell me whether junit supports .net applications. If its not supporting can u help me in knowing the tools which does support .net applications.

Hope that i get a positive feedback soon

Thanking You


NITIN EARNEST PALLAN
